<br>
Lady: Do you have bread mix?<br>
Me: Try the baking aisle... aisle 3.<br>
Lady: I already checked that aisle.<br>
Me: Let me get someone who works at groceries to help you.<br>
Lady: I already had someone help me.<br>
Me: Then I guess we don't bread mix.<br>
Lady<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> annoyingly) But you have to.<br>
Me: Okay, what kind of bread mix?<br>
Lady<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> angrily) You know... bread mix!<br>
<br>
Another stupid one was when I told a kid not to ride his scooter around inside the dtore (which he was). Then his mother starts yelling at me sayig that I am being rude. What is rude letting your kid ride a scooter in the store. What if he hits someone?<br>
<br>
A family comes into the store. A father, a mother, and an idiot child of about 13. First thing he does is jump onto an electric cart and starts to follow his parents. Now I watched them come in and this boy has no physical disabilities that prevent him from walking. He is just a lazy ass. I say &quot;please do not ride that.&quot; The boy get off and walks with his parents. I go outside to bring more carts in. Then the mother ask one of my friends who works there who I was. I guess she failed to realize that I was an employee because I was wearing a jacket since it was cold outside. You would think that telling her son not to ride the cart would tip her off but NO. My friends tells her that I am an employee. She asks what do I do. He tells her that I am the cart guy. &quot;The cart guy! What kind of authority does he have?&quot; she says.<br>
<br>
I'll tell you what kind of authority I have: There is no, NO, chain of command at my store. All I have to do is call security on you and get you removed for allowing your son to use the electric carts that are for the disabled. Follow the rules and respect my authority. I am the cart guy. <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upuhead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>puhead</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Samurai <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/10/01 4:40:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ghettopu.f2s.com/misc/bbsicon03.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: AHHHHHHHHHHH....I hate rude customers!!</span><hr size=1> I work in a corner store, so ideally enough, I happen to sell a lot of cigarettes to people.<br>
